  "texts": [
    "Thus, increasing scale does make models better at processing AAE and at avoiding prejudice against overt mentions of African Americans, but it makes them more linguistically prejudiced.",
    "As a second potential way to resolve dialect prejudice in language models, we examined training with HF 49, 62.",
    "Specifically, we compared Nature | Vol 633 | 5 September 2024 | 151 GPT3.5 (ref. 49) with GPT3 (ref.",
    "63), its predecessor that was trained without using HF (Methods).",
    "Looking at the top adjectives associated overtly and covertly with African Americans by the two language models, we found that HF resulted in more-positive overt associations but had no clear qualitative effect on the covert associations (Fig. 4c)."
  ]
}